Patient should be adequately positioned in ICU bed, with neck extension when feasible. After skin preparation and positioning of sterile fields, preparation of the COVID-Box follows. Firstly, all suction tubes and electrosurgical equipment are positioned on the top of patient's core, securely placed by towel clamps. We made an adaption on the electrosurgical hand piece, placing the tip of the surgical pencil through a 12Fr disposable PVC suction catheter, in order to continuing aspirate aerosols generated by the electric scalpel (figure 2
). Secondly, the COVID-Box metallic structure (sterilized) is placed on top of the draped patient in the UCI bed, then the sterile plastic sheet is positioned above the metallic structure, forming a box-shaped enclosed device. Sterile towel clamps may be used to tighten up the box outer shape (figure 3
a). The access ports on the COVID-Box are then created by cross-shape incisions made at the plastic sheets, two on each side, at the height of surgeon's arms (figure 3b). Another extra port should be created on the caudal part of the COVID-Box, which may be used for instrumentation.
